-- China Says World Needs Currency Stablization Mechanism, PBOC Adviser Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-03T23:58:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/china-needs-world-currency-stablization-mechanism-pboc-adviser-xia-writes.html
Chinese central bank adviser Xia Bin
called for an exchange rate stablization mechanism for major
currencies, according to a commentary published in Financial
News today.  China should set up a department directly under the State
Council to pursue a “prudent macroeconomic” policy, Xia wrote
in the commentary.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
